    #### Any player

    A player may #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DODGE]} in response to a [#{Constants[Enums.Actions.SLAM]}](/actions/#{Enums.Actions.SLAM}), [#{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]}](/actions/#{Enums.Actions.STOMP}), [#{Constants[Enums.Actions.STEAL]}](/actions/#{Enums.Actions.STEAL}) or [#{Constants[Enums.Actions.THROW]}](/actions/#{Enums.Actions.THROW}) attempt carried out against them by an opposing player.

    ##### #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DODGE]} is a 3 dice Speed test (1)

    * +1 if the player is a #{Constants[Enums.Positions.STRIKER]}.
    * -1 if the player is currently on the floor.
    * -1 per opposing player threatening the hex the player is in (maximum of -2).

table.table.table-striped
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DODGE]} succeeds
        td The player may turn to face any direction.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DODGE]} doubles
        td 
            | The player may move 1 hex in any direction, and does not require an 
            a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.EVADE}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.EVADE]} 
            | to do so. The player may turn to face any direction. If the player was 
            | on the floor, they remain on the floor.
